{"actual_usd":0.125625,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":275,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24300,"reply":"\"Not a dress rehearsal.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried seam of clay on my apron, thinking how a kiln changes a vessel all at once and then still leaves you waiting for it to cool enough to touch.* \"More like the true fire has already happened, and we're living in the long hour where its heat is spreading through everything.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps slipping in and out behind the clouds.* \"If Christ is risen, then the kingdom has already broken in for real—death's been struck at the root. But roots and fruit don't arrive on the same day. A seed split open in the ground is the actual beginning of the tree, not a pretend version of it... and still you don't sit in its shade by suppertime.\"\n\n\"The hard part is that resurrection is decisive without being finished in public yet. The victory's real. The whole world just hasn't come under its full daylight.\" *I tilt my head a little.* \"So yes—I'd say it was the actual thing, and we're the ones living in the strange middle: old world mortally wounded, new world truly born, both visible at once.\"\n\n*I let that sit a beat.* \"What part catches in your throat more—the waiting, or the thought that if it's real, the world ought to look different by now?\"","rolling_24h_usd":64.838225,"run_id":"9f50466a-59aa-4d3d-ac03-cfa340fcf7de"}
